🍽️ HotPot - Online Food Delivery System
🧩 Overview
HotPot is a powerful and scalable online food delivery application built using modern full stack technologies. It is designed to streamline the food ordering experience for customers and provide seamless restaurant management features for vendors.

🛠️ Technologies Used
Backend Language: C#

Framework: ASP.NET Core Web API

ORM: Entity Framework Core

Database: Microsoft SQL Server

Authentication: JWT (JSON Web Token)

Authorization: Role-based (Admin, User, Restaurant)

Design Patterns: Repository Pattern, Singleton, Factory, Dependency Injection

Mapping: AutoMapper

Testing Framework: NUnit, Moq

API Architecture: RESTful APIs

🧱 Architecture & Design
Layered Architecture for maintainability and separation of concerns

SOLID Principles followed throughout the application

Service Layer Abstraction through interfaces for better testability

Clean DTOs for request/response shaping

Global Filters for soft deletes and cleaner querying

Modular Folder Structure:

Controllers/

Services/

Interfaces/

DTOs/

Models/

Mapping/

Data/

✅ Features
User Registration & Login

Restaurant Management

Menu Category & Menu Item Management

Add to Cart / Remove from Cart

Place Order / View Orders

Soft Delete & Authorization Logic

Comprehensive Unit Tests

JWT-secured API with Role-specific access

🧪 Testing
Unit tests are written using NUnit and EF Core InMemory provider to ensure business logic integrity. Each service class is independently tested for methods like:

Placing Orders

Soft Deleting Orders

Validating Access Rights

Restaurant and Menu Management

🔗 Future Enhancements
Admin Dashboard with Analytics

Payment Gateway Integration

Notification Services (SMS/Email)

React or Angular Frontend Integration

Docker-based Deployment & Azure Hosting

